nkish) origin, originally a short form of a compound name starting with <i>witu</i> ‘wood’ or <i>wīt</i> ‘wide’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England. In Old French initial <i>w-</i> regularly became <i>gu-</i>. The usual Norman forms of the name were <i>Gy</i> or <i>Guido</i>. In medieval Latin the same name is found as <i>Wido</i>. It was a popular name among the Normans, enhanced no doubt by the romance of Guy of Warwick, recounting the exploits of a folk hero of the Crusades."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Guy De Vignory V was born about 1124, in Europe, his father, Guy IV de Vignory, was 35 and his mother, Alais de Traynel, was 35. He married Mrs. Tiphaine Vignory. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died after 1150."},"et":{"about 1124–AFT 1150":"umbes 1124–pärast 1150","1105–1160":"1105–1160","1105–Female":"1105–Surnud","1124–1150":"1124–1150","1130–Female":"1130–Surnud","1120–1145":"1120–1145","1141–1191":"1141–1191","1145–1165":"1145–1165","1090–1147":"1090–1147","1090":"1090","AFT 1145":"pärast 1145","1165":"1165","1120":"1120","abt 1141":"umbes 1141","Cir 1145":"1145","1141":"1141","1130":"1130","1150":"1150","1160":"1160","1191":"1191","1105":"1105","1147":"1147","1124":"1124","1145":"1145","about 1124":"umbes 1124","AFT 1150":"pärast 1150","Vignory, Haute-Marne, Champagne-Ardenne, France":"Vignory, Haute-Marne, Champagne-Ardenne, Prantsusmaa","Europe":"Europe","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"about 1124–AFT 1150":"noin 1124–1150 jälkeen","1105–1160":"1105–1160","1105–Female":"1105–Kuollut","1124–1150":"1124–1150","1130–Female":"1130–Kuollut","1120–1145":"1120–1145","1141–1191":"1141–1191","1145–1165":"1145–1165","1090–1147":"1090–1147","1090":"1090","AFT 1145":"1145 jälkeen","1165":"1165","1120":"1120","abt 1141":"noin 1141","Cir 1145":"1145","1141":"1141","1130":"1130","1150":"1150","1160":"1160","1191":"1191","1105":"1105","1147":"1147","1124":"1124","1145":"1145","about 1124":"noin 1124","AFT 1